Located at New York Ave. and New Jersey Ave, this location has been a local favorite of Dumbar HS students,  the # 2 Boys and Girls Club, The Old Perry School, and local residents for over 35 years. There is no parking. The owner is Andy.  Kim a family member,  is on the cash register, and Andy and his wife prepare all meals. Orders are also called in by local government workers. Firemen and police officers stop in for a quick bite. Prices are affordable and house favorites are fish sandwiches, pork chop platters, chicken options, hot dogs, hamburgers, seafood options, breakfast, lunch and dinner specials. There are countless others. Portions are large and you don't mind the wait.They are also known for their homemade fruit punch lemonade and ice tea which the students love. The small places are often the best. Definitely a best kept local secret.
